    @InheritOnly
public interface AbstractThrowingToLongFunctionN<H extends AbstractThrowingToLongFunctionN.Handler>
extends AbstractThrowingFunctionN<java.lang.Long,H>
    Represents a function that accepts n arguments and produces a long-valued result or throws a throwable. This is the long-producing primitive specialization for AbstractThrowingFunctionN. All long-producing functions are derived from this n-arity specialization. This is the throwing variation of ToLongFunctionN.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    See Also:
    AbstractThrowingFunctionN, ToLongFunctionN
    API Note:
    This is an abstract consumer and should not be used directly. It should instead be called by one of its subtypes.
